dellNetBpStatsMib.name: dellNetBpStatsMib
dellNetBpStatsMib.description: Dell Networking OS Back plane statistics mib. This is MIB shall use for all back plane statistics related activities. This includes the BP ports traffic statistics. BP link bundle monitoring based on BP port statistics. Queue statistics and buffer utilization on BP ports etc ..

bpLinkBundleRateInterval.name: bpLinkBundleRateInterval
bpLinkBundleRateInterval.description: The rate interval for polling the Bp link bundle Monitoring.

bpLinkBundleTriggerThreshold.name: bpLinkBundleTriggerThreshold
bpLinkBundleTriggerThreshold.description: The traffic distribution trigger threshold for Bp link bundle Monitoring.In percentage of total bandwidth of the link Bundle

bpDropsTable.name: bpDropsTable
bpDropsTable.description: The back plane drops table contains the list of various drops per BP higig port per BCM unit in a stack unit(card type).

bpDropsEntry.name: bpDropsEntry
bpDropsEntry.description: Each drops entry is being indexed by StackUnit(card Type) BCM unit ID and local Port Id

bpDropsStackUnitIndex.name: bpDropsStackUnitIndex
bpDropsStackUnitIndex.description: Stack unit(Card Type Id) number where this port present Each card shall contain more than one BCM units

bpDropsPortPipe.name: bpDropsPortPipe
bpDropsPortPipe.description: bpPortPipe denotes the BCM unit in the stack unit(card Type) Each BCM unit shall contain 1-128 local ports, which includes BP as well as front end ports

bpDropsPortIndex.name: bpDropsPortIndex
bpDropsPortIndex.description: BP port number. Maximum ports shall support by Trident2 BCM npu is 128. This address space includes FE ports also, which are invalid ports as far as BP is concern. For Z9000 leaf BCM units, 34 to 41 are the valid BP port numbers and for spine BCM units, 1 to 16 are the valid BP ports

bpDropsInDrops.name: bpDropsInDrops
bpDropsInDrops.description: The No of Ingress packet Drops

bpDropsInUnKnownHgHdr.name: bpDropsInUnKnownHgHdr
bpDropsInUnKnownHgHdr.description: The No of Unknown hiGig header Ingress packet Drops

bpDropsInUnKnownHgOpcode.name: bpDropsInUnKnownHgOpcode
bpDropsInUnKnownHgOpcode.description: The No of Unknown hiGig Opcode Ingress packet Drops

bpDropsInMTUExceeds.name: bpDropsInMTUExceeds
bpDropsInMTUExceeds.description: No of packets dropped on Ingress because of MTUExceeds

bpDropsInMacDrops.name: bpDropsInMacDrops
bpDropsInMacDrops.description: No of packets dropped on Ingress MAC

bpDropsMMUHOLDrops.name: bpDropsMMUHOLDrops
bpDropsMMUHOLDrops.description: No of packets dropped in MMU because of MMU HOL Drops

bpDropsEgMacDrops.name: bpDropsEgMacDrops
bpDropsEgMacDrops.description: No of packets dropped on Egress MAC

bpDropsEgTxAgedCounter.name: bpDropsEgTxAgedCounter
bpDropsEgTxAgedCounter.description: No of Aged packets dropped on Egress

bpDropsEgTxErrCounter.name: bpDropsEgTxErrCounter
bpDropsEgTxErrCounter.description: No of Error packets dropped on Egress

bpDropsEgTxMACUnderflow.name: bpDropsEgTxMACUnderflow
bpDropsEgTxMACUnderflow.description: No of MAC underflow packets dropped on Egress

bpDropsEgTxErrPktCounter.name: bpDropsEgTxErrPktCounter
bpDropsEgTxErrPktCounter.description: No of total packets dropped in Egress

bpIfStatsTable.name: bpIfStatsTable
bpIfStatsTable.description: The back plane counter statistics table contains the list of various counters per BP higig port per BCM unit in a stack unit(card type).

bpIfStatsEntry.name: bpIfStatsEntry
bpIfStatsEntry.description: Each Stats entry is being indexed by StackUnit(card Type) BCM unit ID and local Port Id

bpIfStatsStackUnitIndex.name: bpIfStatsStackUnitIndex
bpIfStatsStackUnitIndex.description: Stack unit(Card Type Id) number where this port present Each card shall contain more than one BCM units

bpIfStatsPortPipe.name: bpIfStatsPortPipe
bpIfStatsPortPipe.description: bpPortPipe denotes the BCM unit in the stack unit(card Type) Each BCM unit shall contain 1-128 local ports, which includes BP as well as front end ports

bpIfStatsPortIndex.description: BP port number. Maximum ports shall support by Trident2 BCM npu is 128. This address space includes FE ports also, which are invalid ports as far as BP is concern. bpIfStatsIn64BytePkts.name: bpIfStatsIn64BytePkts
bpIfStatsIn64BytePkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were 64 octets in length (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

bpIfStatsIn65To127BytePkts.name: bpIfStatsIn65To127BytePkts
bpIfStatsIn65To127BytePkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 65 and 127 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

bpIfStatsIn128To255BytePkts.name: bpIfStatsIn128To255BytePkts
bpIfStatsIn128To255BytePkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 128 and 255 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

bpIfStatsIn256To511BytePkts.name: bpIfStatsIn256To511BytePkts
bpIfStatsIn256To511BytePkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 256 and 511 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

bpIfStatsIn512To1023BytePkts.name: bpIfStatsIn512To1023BytePkts
bpIfStatsIn512To1023BytePkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 512 and 1023 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

bpIfStatsInOver1023BytePkts.name: bpIfStatsInOver1023BytePkts
bpIfStatsInOver1023BytePkts.description: The total number of frames received that were longer than 1023 (1025 Bytes in case of VLAN Tag) octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed. This counter is not incremented for too long frames.

bpIfStatsInThrottles.name: bpIfStatsInThrottles
bpIfStatsInThrottles.description: This counter is incremented when a valid frame with a length or type field value equal to 0x8808 (Control Frame) is received.

bpIfStatsInRunts.name: bpIfStatsInRunts
bpIfStatsInRunts.description: The total number of frames received that were less than 64 octets long (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed.

bpIfStatsInGiants.name: bpIfStatsInGiants
bpIfStatsInGiants.description: The total number of frames received that were longer than 1518 (1522 Bytes in case of VLAN Tag) octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed. This counter is not incremented for too long frames.

bpIfStatsInCRC.name: bpIfStatsInCRC
bpIfStatsInCRC.description: The total number of frames received that had a length (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) of between 64 and 1518 octets, inclusive, but had a bad CRC.

bpIfStatsInOverruns.name: bpIfStatsInOverruns
bpIfStatsInOverruns.description: The total number of frames has been chosen to be dropped by detecting the buffer issue

bpIfStatsOutUnderruns.name: bpIfStatsOutUnderruns
bpIfStatsOutUnderruns.description: The total number of frames dropped because of buffer underrun.

bpIfStatsOutUnicasts.name: bpIfStatsOutUnicasts
bpIfStatsOutUnicasts.description: The total number of Unicast frames are transmitted out of the interface

bpIfStatsOutCollisions.name: bpIfStatsOutCollisions
bpIfStatsOutCollisions.description: A count of the frames that due to excessive or late collisions are not transmitted successfully.

bpIfStatsOutWredDrops.name: bpIfStatsOutWredDrops
bpIfStatsOutWredDrops.description: The total number of frames are dropped by using WRED policy due to excessive traffic.

bpIfStatsOut64BytePkts.name: bpIfStatsOut64BytePkts
bpIfStatsOut64BytePkts.description: The total number of valid frames with the block of 64 byte size is transmitted

bpIfStatsOut65To127BytePkts.name: bpIfStatsOut65To127BytePkts
bpIfStatsOut65To127BytePkts.description: The total of valid frame with the block size of range between 65 and 127 bytes are transmitted.

bpIfStatsOut128To255BytePkts.name: bpIfStatsOut128To255BytePkts
bpIfStatsOut128To255BytePkts.description: The total of valid frame with the block size of range between 128 and 255 bytes are transmitted

bpIfStatsOut256To511BytePkts.name: bpIfStatsOut256To511BytePkts
bpIfStatsOut256To511BytePkts.description: The total of valid frame with the block size of range between 256 and 511 bytes are transmitted

bpIfStatsOut512To1023BytePkts.name: bpIfStatsOut512To1023BytePkts
bpIfStatsOut512To1023BytePkts.description: The total of valid frame with the block size of range between 512 and 1023 bytes are transmitted

bpIfStatsOutOver1023BytePkts.name: bpIfStatsOutOver1023BytePkts
bpIfStatsOutOver1023BytePkts.description: The total of valid frame with the block size of greater than 1023 bytes are transmitted.

bpIfStatsOutThrottles.name: bpIfStatsOutThrottles
bpIfStatsOutThrottles.description: This counter is incremented when a valid frame with a length or type field value equal to 0x8808 (Control Frame) is sent.

bpIfStatsLastDiscontinuityTime.name: bpIfStatsLastDiscontinuityTime
bpIfStatsLastDiscontinuityTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which this interface's counters suffered a discontinuity via a reset. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

bpIfStatsInCentRate.name: bpIfStatsInCentRate
bpIfStatsInCentRate.description: This is the percentage of maximum line rate at which data is receiving on the Interface. For Z9000 - BP hiGig line rate is 42G. This is an integer value which can go from 0% to 100%.

bpIfStatsOutCentRate.name: bpIfStatsOutCentRate
bpIfStatsOutCentRate.description: This is the percentage of maximum line rate at which data is sending on the Interface. For Z9000 - BP hiGig line rate is 42G. This is an integer value which can go from 0% to 100%.

bpIfStatsLastChange.name: bpIfStatsLastChange
bpIfStatsLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime, on which all the counters are updated recently
